Ri referred to a joint statement made by Kim Jong Un and Donald Trump at the first U.S.-Sitting President and North Korean leader summit in Singapore on June 12, in which Kim asserted "the denuclearization of the Korean peninsula" and Trump promised to guarantee North Korea's security.
North Korea has sought to officially end the 1950-1953 Korean War, but the United States has insisted that Pyongyang must first give up its nuclear weapons.
