Red tide algal blooms have also been observed in Pasco County.
Moderate concentrations were reported from the coast of Pinellas County in the past week, concentrations ranging from low to high along the coasts of Hillsborough County, from background levels to high concentrations in Manatee and Sarasota County, from background levels to moderate levels in Charlotte County, and from background levels to high concentrations along the coasts of Lee County and Collier County were low in lengths.
Respiratory symptoms are still reported in the Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier regions.
In the past week, there were no reports of respiratory symptoms in the northwest of Florida.
